In some, a player can only commit to the performance of an  action, in others, he can commit himself conditionally on the actions of the other players.
Some situations even allow for commitments on commitments or for commitments to randomized actions.
We explore the formal properties of these types of (conditional)  commitment and their interrelationships.
So as to preclude  inconsistencies among conditional commitments, we assume an order in which the players make their commitments.
Central to our analyses is the notion of an extortion , which we define , for a given order of the players , as a profile 